#: ../../../contributing.rst:2
msgid "Contributing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:4
msgid ""
"urllib3 is a community-maintained project and we happily accept "
"contributions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:6
msgid "If you wish to add a new feature or fix a bug:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:8
msgid ""
"`Check for open issues <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues>`_ or open "
"a fresh issue to start a discussion around a feature idea or a bug. There is "
"a *Contributor Friendly* tag for issues that should be ideal for people who "
"are not very familiar with the codebase yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:12
msgid ""
"Fork the `urllib3 repository on Github <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3>`_ to start making your changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:14
msgid ""
"Write a test which shows that the bug was fixed or that the feature works as "
"expected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:16
msgid ""
"Format your changes with black using command ``nox -rs format`` and lint "
"your changes using command ``nox -rs lint``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:18
msgid ""
"Add a `changelog entry <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/blob/main/"
"changelog/README.rst>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:20
msgid ""
"Send a pull request and bug the maintainer until it gets merged and "
"published."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:24
msgid "Setting up your development environment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:26
msgid ""
"In order to setup the development environment all that you need is `nox "
"<https://nox.thea.codes/en/stable/index.html>`_ installed in your machine::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:29
msgid "$ python -m pip install --user --upgrade nox"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:33
msgid "Running the tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:35
msgid ""
"We use some external dependencies, multiple interpreters and code coverage "
"analysis while running test suite. Our ``noxfile.py`` handles much of this "
"for you::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:39
msgid ""
"$ nox --reuse-existing-virtualenvs --sessions test-3.12 test-pypy3.10\n"
"[ Nox will create virtualenv if needed, install the specified dependencies, "
"and run the commands in order.]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:43
msgid ""
"Note that for nox to test different interpreters, the interpreters must be "
"on the ``PATH`` first. Check with ``which`` to see if the interpreter is on "
"the ``PATH`` like so::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:48
msgid ""
"$ which python3.12\n"
"~/.pyenv/versions/3.12.1/bin/python3.12\n"
"\n"
"$ which pypy3.10\n"
"~/.pyenv/versions/pypy3.10-7.3.13/bin/pypy3.10"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:55
msgid ""
"There is also a nox command for running all of our tests and multiple python "
"versions.::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:58
msgid "$ nox --reuse-existing-virtualenvs --sessions test"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:60
msgid ""
"Note that code coverage less than 100% is regarded as a failing run. Some "
"platform-specific tests are skipped unless run in that platform.  To make "
"sure the code works in all of urllib3's supported platforms, you can run our "
"``nox`` suite::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:65
msgid ""
"$ nox --reuse-existing-virtualenvs --sessions test\n"
"[ Nox will create virtualenv if needed, install the specified dependencies, "
"and run the commands in order.]\n"
".......\n"
".......\n"
"nox > Session test-3.9 was successful.\n"
"nox > Session test-3.10 was successful.\n"
"nox > Session test-3.11 was successful.\n"
"nox > Session test-3.12 was successful.\n"
"nox > Session test-3.13 was successful.\n"
"nox > Session test-3.14 was successful.\n"
"nox > Session test-3.15 was successful.\n"
"nox > Session test-pypy was successful."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:78
msgid ""
"Our test suite `runs continuously on GitHub Actions <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/actions>`_ with every pull request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:81
msgid ""
"To run specific tests or quickly re-run without nox recreating the env, do "
"the following::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:83
msgid ""
"$ nox --reuse-existing-virtualenvs --sessions test-3.13 -- pyTestArgument1 "
"pyTestArgument2 pyTestArgumentN\n"
"[ Nox will create virtualenv, install the specified dependencies, and run "
"the commands in order.]\n"
"nox > Running session test-3.13\n"
"nox > Re-using existing virtual environment at .nox/test-3-13.\n"
".......\n"
".......\n"
"nox > Session test-3.13 was successful."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:91
msgid ""
"After the ``--`` indicator, any arguments will be passed to pytest. To "
"specify an exact test case the following syntax also works: ``test/dir/"
"module_name.py::TestClassName::test_method_name`` (eg.: ``test/"
"with_dummyserver/test_https.py::TestHTTPS::test_simple``). The following "
"argument is another valid example to pass to pytest: ``-k "
"test_methode_name``. These are useful when developing new test cases and "
"there is no point re-running the entire test suite every iteration. It is "
"also possible to further parameterize pytest for local testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:100
msgid ""
"For all valid arguments, check `the pytest documentation <https://docs."
"pytest.org/en/stable/usage.html#stopping-after-the-first-or-n-failures>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:104
msgid "Getting paid for your contributions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:106
msgid ""
"urllib3 has a `pool of money hosted on Open Collective <https://"
"opencollective.com/urllib3#category-BUDGET>`_ which the team uses to pay "
"contributors for their work. **That could be you, too!** If you complete all "
"tasks in an issue that is marked with the `\"💰 Bounty $X00\" label <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues?"
"q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3A%22%F0%9F%92%B0+Bounty+"
"%24100%22%2C%22%F0%9F%92%B0+Bounty+%24200%22%2C%22%F0%9F%92%B0+Bounty+"
"%24300%22%2C%22%F0%9F%92%B0+Bounty+%24400%22%2C%22%F0%9F%92%B0+Bounty+"
"%24500%22+no%3Aassignee>`_ then you're eligible to be paid for your work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:110
msgid ""
"Ensure that you're able to `receive funds from Open Collective for working "
"on OSS <https://docs.opencollective.com/help/expenses-and-getting-paid/"
"submitting-expenses>`_. Consider your employment contract and taxes for "
"possible restrictions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:112
msgid ""
"If an issue is already assigned to someone on GitHub then it's likely "
"they've made substantial progress on the issue and will be given the bounty. "
"If you're interested in bounties you should look for issues which aren't "
"assigned to anyone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:116
msgid ""
"**Don't \"claim\" issues or ask whether someone is already working on an "
"issue.** Instead, focus on researching and working on the tasks in the "
"issue. Once you have made considerable progress on the tasks in an issue we "
"can assign your account to the issue to ensure others don't start working on "
"it in parallel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:120
msgid ""
"If you've been assigned to an issue and haven't made progress or given an "
"update in over a week you will be unassigned from the issue to allow others "
"a chance at solving the issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:123
msgid ""
"The amount you will be paid for the completing an issue is shown in the "
"label (either $100, $200, $300, etc)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:124
msgid ""
"If you have questions about how to create an invoice on Open Collective `try "
"reading their FAQ <https://docs.opencollective.com/help/expenses-and-getting-"
"paid/expenses>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:126
msgid ""
"If you have a proposal to work on urllib3 that's not listed in the issue "
"tracker please open an issue with your proposal and our team will discuss "
"whether we'd pay for your work on your proposal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:128
msgid ""
"If you have other questions get in contact with a maintainer in the `urllib3 "
"Discord channel <https://discord.gg/urllib3>`_ or via email."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:129
msgid ""
"The list above isn't an exhaustive list of criteria or rules for how/when "
"money is distributed. **The final say on whether money will be distributed "
"is up to maintainers.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:132
msgid ""
"This program is an experiment so if you have positive or negative feedback "
"on the process you can contact the maintainers through one of the above "
"channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:134
msgid ""
"Note that this program isn't a \"bug bounty\" program, we don't distribute "
"funds to reporters of bugs or security vulnerabilities at this time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:137
msgid "Running local proxies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:139
msgid ""
"If the feature you are developing involves a proxy, you can rely on scripts "
"we have developed to run a proxy locally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:141
msgid "Run an HTTP proxy locally:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:143
msgid "$ python -m dummyserver.proxy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:147
msgid "Run an HTTPS proxy locally:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:149
msgid "$ python -m dummyserver.https_proxy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:154
msgid "Contributing to documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:156
msgid "You can build the docs locally using ``nox``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:158
msgid "$ nox -rs docs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:162
msgid "While writing documentation you should follow these guidelines:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:164
msgid ""
"Use the top-level ``urllib3.request()`` function for smaller code examples. "
"For more involved examples use PoolManager, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:165
msgid "Use double quotes for all strings. (Output, Declaration etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:166
msgid ""
"Use keyword arguments everywhere except for method and url. (ie ``http."
"request(\"GET\", \"https://example.com\", headers={...})`` )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:167
msgid "Use HTTPS in URLs everywhere unless HTTP is needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:168
msgid "Rules for code examples and naming variables:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:170
msgid ""
"``PoolManager`` instances should be named ``http``. (ie ``http = urllib3."
"PoolManager(...)``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:171
msgid "``ProxyManager`` instances should be named ``proxy``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:172
msgid "``ConnectionPool`` instances should be named ``pool``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:173
msgid "``Connection`` instances should be named ``conn``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:174
msgid "``HTTPResponse`` instances should be named ``resp``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:175
msgid "Only use ``example.com`` or ``httpbin.org`` for example URLs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:177
msgid ""
"Comments within snippets should be useful, if what's being done is apparent "
"(such as parsing JSON, making a request) then it can be skipped for that "
"section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:179
msgid ""
"Comments should always go above a code section rather than below with the "
"exception of print statements where the comment containing the result goes "
"below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:181
msgid ""
"Imports should be their own section separated from the rest of the example "
"with a line of whitespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:182
msgid ""
"Imports should minimized if possible. Use import urllib3 instead of from "
"urllib3 import X."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:183
msgid ""
"Sort imports similarly to isort, standard library first and third-party "
"(like urllib3) come after."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:184
msgid ""
"No whitespace is required between the sections as normally would be in case "
"of isort."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:185
msgid ""
"Add print statements along with a comment below them showing the output, "
"potentially compressed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:186
msgid ""
"This helps users using the copy-paste button immediately see the results "
"from a script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:189
msgid "Releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:191
msgid "A release candidate can be created by any contributor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:193
msgid ""
"Announce intent to release on Discord, see if anyone wants to include last "
"minute changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:195
msgid ""
"Run ``towncrier build`` to update ``CHANGES.rst`` with the release notes, "
"adjust as necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:197
msgid "Commit the changes to a ``release-X.Y.Z`` branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:198
msgid ""
"Create a pull request and append ``&expand=1&template=release.md`` to the "
"URL before submitting in order to include our release checklist in the pull "
"request description."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:200
msgid "Follow the checklist!"
msgstr ""
